  "chapter": {
    "number": 7,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Job Continues: Life Seems Futile"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Is not man consigned to labor on earth?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Are not his days like those of a hired hand?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Like a slave he longs for shade;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a hireling he waits for his wages.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So I am allotted months of futility,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and nights of misery are appointed me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When I lie down I think:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘When will I get up?’",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "But the night drags on,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I toss and turn until dawn.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My flesh is clothed with worms",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and encrusted with dirt;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "my skin is cracked and festering.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My days are swifter than a weaver’s shuttle;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they come to an end without hope.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Remember that my life is but a breath.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "My eyes will never again see happiness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The eye that beholds me will no longer see me.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You will look for me, but I will be no more.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "As a cloud vanishes and is gone,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so he who goes down to Sheol does not come back up.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He never returns to his house;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "his place remembers him no more.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore I will not restrain my mouth;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will speak in the anguish of my spirit;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will complain in the bitterness of my soul.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Am I the sea, or the monster of the deep,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that You must keep me under guard?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When I think my bed will comfort me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and my couch will ease my complaint,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "then You frighten me with dreams",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and terrify me with visions,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "so that I would prefer strangling and death",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "over my life in this body.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I loathe my life! I would not live forever.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Leave me alone, for my days are but a breath.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What is man that You should exalt him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that You should set Your heart upon him,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "that You attend to him every morning,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and test him every moment?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Will You never look away from me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or leave me alone to swallow my spittle?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If I have sinned, what have I done to You,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O watcher of mankind?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Why have You made me Your target,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that I am a burden to You",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3157
          },
          {
            "text": "?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why do You not pardon my transgression",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and take away my iniquity?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For soon I will lie down in the dust;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You will seek me, but I will be no more.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
